<h1 class="ds-page-title">Delete something</h1>
<p class="ds-page-lead">
    Deleting items requires confirmation to prevent accidental data loss. COMPASS supports two variants: delete as a link and delete as a button. Both should show a confirmation modal with a red delete button.
</p>

<h2>Delete as a link</h2>
<p>
    Use delete links in tables, lists, or when space is limited. The link should trigger a confirmation modal.
</p>

<div class="component-example">
    <div class="component-example-title">Example - Delete link in table</div>
    <table class="table table-striped">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Item</th>
                <th>Status</th>
                <th>Actions</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>Project Alpha</td>
                <td><span class="dfe-adminui-badge dfe-adminui-badge--success">Active</span></td>
                <td>
                    <a href="#" class="dfe-adminui-text-danger" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#deleteLinkModal">
                        <i class="fas fa-trash" aria-hidden="true"></i> Delete
                    </a>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
</div>

<!-- Delete Link Modal -->
<div class="modal fade" id="deleteLinkModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="deleteLinkModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <h5 class="modal-title" id="deleteLinkModalLabel">Confirm deletion</h5>
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
                    <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
                </button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <div class="dfe-adminui-alert dfe-adminui-alert--warning" role="alert">
                    <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle mr-2" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    <strong>Warning:</strong> This action cannot be undone. Are you sure you want to delete "Project Alpha"?
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-dismiss="modal">Cancel</button>
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-danger">Delete</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<pre><code>&lt;!-- Delete link --&gt;
&lt;a href="#" class="dfe-adminui-text-danger" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#deleteModal"&gt;
    &lt;i class="fas fa-trash" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Delete
&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;!-- Delete confirmation modal --&gt;
&lt;div class="modal fade" id="deleteModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog"&gt;
    &lt;div class="modal-dialog" role="document"&gt;
        &lt;div class="modal-content"&gt;
            &lt;div class="modal-header"&gt;
                &lt;h5 class="modal-title"&gt;Confirm deletion&lt;/h5&gt;
                &lt;button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal"&gt;
                    &lt;span aria-hidden="true"&gt;&times;&lt;/span&gt;
                &lt;/button&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div class="modal-body"&gt;
                &lt;div class="dfe-adminui-alert dfe-adminui-alert--warning"&gt;
                    &lt;strong&gt;Warning:&lt;/strong&gt; This action cannot be undone.
                &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div class="modal-footer"&gt;
                &lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-dismiss="modal"&gt;Cancel&lt;/button&gt;
                &lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-danger"&gt;Delete&lt;/button&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>

<h2>Delete as a button</h2>
<p>
    Use delete buttons in forms, card actions, or when the delete action is a primary action. The button should trigger a confirmation modal.
</p>

<div class="component-example">
    <div class="component-example-title">Example - Delete button</div>
    <div class="card">
        <div class="dfe-adminui-card__header">
            <h3 class="card-title">Project settings</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="dfe-adminui-card__body">
            <p>Manage project settings and configuration.</p>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-danger" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#deleteButtonModal">
                <i class="fas fa-trash mr-2" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                Delete project
            </button>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Delete Button Modal -->
<div class="modal fade" id="deleteButtonModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="deleteButtonModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <h5 class="modal-title" id="deleteButtonModalLabel">Confirm deletion</h5>
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
                    <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
                </button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <div class="dfe-adminui-alert dfe-adminui-alert--warning" role="alert">
                    <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle mr-2" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    <strong>Warning:</strong> This action cannot be undone. Are you sure you want to delete this project?
                </div>
                <p>All associated data will be permanently removed.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-dismiss="modal">Cancel</button>
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-danger">Delete</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<pre><code>&lt;!-- Delete button --&gt;
&lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-danger" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#deleteModal"&gt;
    &lt;i class="fas fa-trash mr-2"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
    Delete project
&lt;/button&gt;

&lt;!-- Delete confirmation modal --&gt;
&lt;div class="modal fade" id="deleteModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog"&gt;
    &lt;div class="modal-dialog" role="document"&gt;
        &lt;div class="modal-content"&gt;
            &lt;div class="modal-header"&gt;
                &lt;h5 class="modal-title"&gt;Confirm deletion&lt;/h5&gt;
                &lt;button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal"&gt;
                    &lt;span aria-hidden="true"&gt;&times;&lt;/span&gt;
                &lt;/button&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div class="modal-body"&gt;
                &lt;div class="dfe-adminui-alert dfe-adminui-alert--warning"&gt;
                    &lt;strong&gt;Warning:&lt;/strong&gt; This action cannot be undone.
                &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div class="modal-footer"&gt;
                &lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-dismiss="modal"&gt;Cancel&lt;/button&gt;
                &lt;button type="button" class="btn btn-danger"&gt;Delete&lt;/button&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>

<h2>Usage guidelines</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Delete as link:</strong> Use in tables, lists, or when space is limited. Style with <code>text-danger</code> class.</li>
    <li><strong>Delete as button:</strong> Use in forms, card actions, or when delete is a primary action. Use <code>btn-danger</code> class.</li>
    <li>Always require explicit confirmation via modal before deleting</li>
    <li>Show a clear warning message explaining the consequences</li>
    <li>Use red/danger styling for delete buttons in the modal</li>
    <li>Provide a "Cancel" option that is easily accessible</li>
    <li>Consider soft deletes (marking as deleted) instead of hard deletes when possible</li>
    <li>Include the item name in the confirmation message when relevant</li>
</ul>

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Ensure confirmation modals are keyboard accessible</li>
    <li>Provide clear labels for all buttons</li>
    <li>Use appropriate ARIA roles for dialogs (<code>role="dialog"</code>)</li>
    <li>Ensure focus management when opening/closing dialogs</li>
    <li>Use <code>aria-labelledby</code> to associate modal title with dialog</li>
    <li>Include <code>aria-hidden="true"</code> on modal backdrop</li>
</ul>
